VThe Music Lovers&#8217; association along with Thyagaraja Gana Sabha, organised a three-day festival of instrumental music for promoting innate talent among the up and coming artistes in the city.The programme was held recently at the mini auditorium of Sri Thyagaraja Gana Sabha, Chikkadpally.Seven-year-old K. Shruti played a sitar of her height. Pandurang Muthalik set the tempo of the concert withMalkaunts.He delivered all the intricacies of the raga.The second day featured short duration concerts of Radhna Saxsena, Irfan Ahmed Khan and K. Vijay Kumar. The concluding day saw K. Niladri Kumar, M. Pushpalatha and Ali Bin Nabid.
